list.abstract: FORCE（英 [fɔːs]，美 [fɔːrs]），是英文单词，作名词为力；力量；强制力量。作动词为强行通过；强行打开；促成。短语搭配有Air Force（空军）。例句为“It came into force about ten years ago.（它大约在十年前生效。）” 该单词的复数形式和第三人称单数为 forces，过去式和过去分词为 forced，名词类近义词为strength、might、army，不及物动词类近义词为bring、drive，反义词为pull、push。
做为漫画的男主角，除了外表的亲和力外，更重要的是他内心深处带给读者的独特感受，也就是隐性的个性。对于这个，我在剧本的设置上会充分考虑到他作为一名普通人和特殊人的区别，佐阳起先带给读者的，一定是普通，低调、神秘 与常见漫画中的男主角比较，在最初的设定上，他的作用更多的是引发事件，带出故事，来展现身边朋友的能力，丰富剧情，对事件最终的解决，初期起启发性的决定作用。

yingyinNormal.en: On the upper deck of the next carriage there is a conductor's compartment. It's a small office containing a strongbox. Inside is a loaded handgun. Get to it. You are authorized to use whatever force necessary.
yingyinNormal.zh: 旁边车厢的二楼有一个乘务员室，里面有一个保险箱，箱内有一把上膛的手枪，找到它，必要时你可以使用任何武力。

yingyinNormal.en: You can't force me to stay in here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不能强迫我留在屋内。

yingyinNormal.en: Copy. Air force one prepped and ready to go.
yingyinNormal.zh: 收到，空军一号已经准备就绪。

yingyinNormal.en: Nearest quick reaction force? Sicily, two hours out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最近的快速反应部队呢？在西西里，两小时路程。

yingyinNormal.en: Pretty soon you're all going to join the work force.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很快你们就会参加工作。

yingyinNormal.en: Shredder will force this city to live under our rule.
yingyinNormal.zh: 施莱德会强迫这座城市在我们的规矩下生活。

yingyinNormal.en: But these two forces, the social force and the market force are not additive, when one comes the other one goes away.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但这两者，社会和市场推动力不是附加的，两者不同时出现。

yingyinNormal.en: Gravity is pretty neat. It's the force that stops us from floating off the planet, but it's not a constant, uniform force.
yingyinNormal.zh: 地心引力非常巧妙，这个力量让我们不会飘离地球 但地心引力不是一直那么稳定。

yingyinNormal.en: The force field. lt's a dome. We're at the edge of the arena.
yingyinNormal.zh: 电磁力场是个拱顶，我们在竞技场的边缘。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, I would, but we need to make a push on the air force project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我愿意去，可我们明天要赶工弄一下空军的项目。

yingyinNormal.en: Then what is it? It's a recruiting tool for a very dangerous force.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是这什么？这是招募，源自一个极度危险的力量。

yingyinNormal.en: How? Force the Chinese to confront the issue now, this round of talks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 怎样做? 下次谈判时，逼迫中方回应网络安全问题。

yingyinNormal.en: Crazy thing is it's true. The Force. The Jedi. All of it. It's all true.
yingyinNormal.zh: 难以置信的是，这是真的。原力，绝地武士，所有一切，都是真的。

yingyinNormal.en: A dark force is growing. A criminal organization known as the Foot Clan.
yingyinNormal.zh: 黑暗的力量正在崛起，一个被人民称為"大脚帮"的犯罪组织 。

yingyinNormal.en: You're very smart. You see they can't rebuild without a slave labor force.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你真聪明，没有奴隶的劳动力，他们无法重建。

yingyinNormal.en: A cold fusion of two universal elements, identical in weight, equal in force.
yingyinNormal.zh: 两个通用元素冷聚变，重量一致，力量均等。

yingyinNormal.en: Then get her detail on the phone. I did. They can't force her to talk to you, sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那就打给她的保安。我打了，他们不能逼她跟您说话，先生。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, I can't force you to see reason. But I will not allow you to become dangerous.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我没法逼你想通道理，但我不允许你成为隐患。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, well, I knew a guy on the force. He had it rough. Talked about eating his gun.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我队上认识个人，他很绝望说要饮弹自尽。

yingyinNormal.en: The Air Force did it again. They're erasing our lives! Third floor, wrong apartment.
yingyinNormal.zh: 美国空军又出手了。他们要抹去我们的生活！这是三楼，走错公寓了。

examination_example.sentence: Nothing is necessarily gained by <highlight>forcing</highlight> students to learn geometry at a graffitied desk stuck with generations of discarded chewing gum.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 强迫学生在堆满了几代人丢弃的口香糖的涂鸦桌前学习几何，肯定不会有什么好处。

examination_example.sentence: This <highlight>forces</highlight> users to be more conscious of their role in passing along information.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这迫使用户更加意识到自己在传递信息中的角色。

examination_example.sentence: That whispered message, half invitation and half <highlight>forcing</highlight>, is what most of us think of when we hear the words peer pressure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我们听到“同辈压力”这个词时，大多数人都会想到这种半是邀请，半是强迫的低语。

sense_info_list.en: strength or energy as an attribute of physical action or movement

examination_example.sentence: But another, related <highlight>force</highlight> — a policy often buried deep in course catalogs called "grade forgiveness" — is helping raise GPAs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是另一种相关的力量——一种经常被深埋在课程目录中的政策，叫做“分数宽恕”——正在帮助提高平均绩点。

examination_example.sentence: But the <highlight>force</highlight> of geographic conditions peculiar to America, the interplay of the varied national groups upon one another caused significant changes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是，由于美国特有的地理条件，以及不同民族群体之间的相互作用，导致了重大的变化。

examination_example.sentence: But in her new book, she contends that peer pressure can also be a positive <highlight>force</highlight> through what she calls the social cure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但在她的新书中，她主张，通过她所谓的社会治疗，同辈压力也可以成为一种积极的力量。

sense_info_list.en: a group of people organized and trained, especially for a particular purpose
sense_info_list.zh: 武装部队; 警察部门; 一群人

examination_example.sentence: The percentage of retirement-age people in the labor <highlight>force</highlight> has doubled over the past three decades.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在过去的三十年里，劳动力中退休年龄人口的比例翻了一番。

examination_example.sentence: Last year a federal task-<highlight>force</highlight> urged reform for patents related to genetic tests.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 去年，一个联邦工作组敦促对基因检测相关的专利进行改革。

examination_example.sentence: 70 percent of king penguins could either disappear or be <highlight>forced</highlight> to find new breeding grounds.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 70%的帝企鹅要么消失，要么被迫寻找新的繁殖地。

examination_example.sentence: Unless current greenhouse gas emissions drop, 70 percent of king penguins will be <highlight>forced</highlight> to relocate their breeding grounds, or face extinction.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 除非当前的温室气体排放量下降，否则将有70％的帝企鹅被迫迁移繁殖地，或者将面临灭绝。

examination_example.sentence: If we're going to <highlight>force</highlight> taxpayers to foot the bill for college degrees, students should only study those subjects that're of greatest benefit to taxpayers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果我们要强迫纳税人为大学学位买单，学生们应该只学习那些对纳税人最有益的科目。

examination_example.sentence: On the flip side, there are many "<highlight>forced</highlight> riders", who are suffering from the climate change impacts despite having scarcely contributed to the problem.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 而另一方面，也有许多“被迫搭车者”，他们是气候变化的受害者，尽管他们并不是造成这一后果主要的罪魁祸首。

examination_example.sentence: Critics of your book assert that you're trying to <highlight>force</highlight> radical changes on the entire country.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 批评你的书的人断言，你试图在整个国家推行激进的变革。

examination_example.sentence: So they're depicting me as a radical animal rights activist and environmentalist determined to <highlight>force</highlight> my beliefs on others.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以他们把我描绘成一个激进的动物权利主义者和环保主义者，决心把我的信仰强加给别人。

examination_example.sentence: I'm not overstating the danger: look at what's happened to the labor <highlight>force</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我并没有夸大危险：看看劳动力发生了什么。

examination_example.sentence: Women's labor <highlight>force</highlight> participation, meanwhile, has slipped back to the level it was at in the late 1980s.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与此同时，女性的劳动力参与率已经回落到20世纪80年代末的水平。

examination_example.sentence: Information technology are having a dramatic impact on jobs most people think are secure from the <highlight>forces</highlight> of a rapidly-changing economy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 信息技术对大多数人认为不受快速变化的经济力量影响的工作产生了巨大的影响。

an influence tending to change the motion of a body or produce motion or stress in a stationary body
make a way through or into by physical strength; break open by force

word_usage.usage: force作为及物动词，表示“强迫”，“迫使”。表示“强迫某人做某事”有2种表达方式: (1) force sb to do sth; (2)  force sb into+ doing sth。
force作名词表示“力量”时，是不可数名词，没有复数形式。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指在法律、权力、力量或行动等的驱使下被迫而为。
侧重施加约束力或有约束作用的影响, 也指环境对人强加的影响迫使人去做某事, 尤指受良心、情感等内在力量驱使去做某事。
指用个人意志、权力、权威或暴力等, 迫使他人改变看法或做本不愿做的事。
指由于生理上或道德上的需要, 促使某人做某事, 也指有权威的人或机构迫使某人做某事, 还可指在特定情况下被迫作出的反应。
用于人时, 指工作时焕发出的精力或干劲。
着重指克服障碍, 推动人或物朝所要求的方向运动或能产生明显效应的力量。
多指巨大或超人的力量。

军队, 着重指军队这个整体, 包括陆海空三军。当与 navy 和 air force 并列使用时, 则指陆军。
如：We will have not only a powerful army but also a powerful air force and a powerful navy.(我们不但要有强大的陆军, 而且要有强大的空军和海军。)
军队, 部队, 着重指武力, 常用复数。语体较正式, 多用复数形式, 既可指包括陆、海、空在内的一个国家的整个武装力量, 也可指某一兵种。如：Forces were sent out to stop the conflict.(派出武装部队制止这场冲突。)

examination_example.sentence: At times, these breaks and transitions will be self-determined, at others they will be <highlight>forced</highlight> as existing roles, firms, or industries cease to exist.

examination_example.sentence: Shifting eating habits, including a sharp drop in consumption of sparkling drinks, have <highlight>forced</highlight> radical change on the industry.

examination_example.sentence: Read books, go to movies, take on new hobbies or activities that <highlight>force</highlight> one to think in novel ways.

word_usage.usage: force作名词表示“力量”时，是不可数名词，没有复数形式。
force作为及物动词，表示“强迫”，“迫使”。表示“强迫某人做某事”有2种表达方式: (1) force sb to do sth; (2)  force sb into+ doing sth。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指在法律、权力、力量或行动等的驱使下被迫而为。
侧重施加约束力或有约束作用的影响，也指环境对人强加的影响迫使人去做某事，尤指受良心、情感等内在力量驱使去做某事。
指用个人意志、权力、权威或暴力等，迫使他人改变看法或做本不愿做的事。
指由于生理上或道德上的需要，促使某人做某事，也指有权威的人或机构迫使某人做某事，还可指在特定情况下被迫作出的反应。
用于人时，指工作时焕发出的精力或干劲。
着重指克服障碍，推动人或物朝所要求的方向运动或能产生明显效应的力量。
多指巨大或超人的力量。

军队，着重指军队这个整体，包括陆海空三军。当与 navy 和 air force 并列使用时，则指陆军。
如：We will have not only a powerful army but also a powerful air force and a powerful navy.(我们不但要有强大的陆军，而且要有强大的空军和海军。)
军队，部队，着重指武力，常用复数。语体较正式，多用复数形式，既可指包括陆、海、空在内的一个国家的整个武装力量，也可指某一兵种。如：Forces were sent out to stop the conflict.(派出武装部队制止这场冲突。)
